post: {'type': 'pro', 'text': '[Ketamine](https://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/322534.php?iacp), a promising alternative to opioids, is currently banned. I believe legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Assuming that drugs will still be legally forbidden for people under a certain age, the distribution points will not be allowed to sell it to children.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Bettering education surrounding date rape and the drugs used for it would improve levels of prevention. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Some drugs will lead to people having hallucinations or becoming violent. In these instances, individuals may be a danger to themselves or others. I believe drugs should remain illegal.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': "This doesn't apply where there is no NHS or equivalent."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Without proper education, people who are more prone to drug addiction may be more likely to get addicted to a drug.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Although education and information on the harmful side effects of [smoking](https://edition.cnn.com/2014/01/11/health/still-smoking/index.html) have been around for decades, millions of people still smoke.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The legalisation of all drugs will promote newer, and safer drugs being developed to combat the negative side effects of dangerous drugs such as methamphetamines or heroin. I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Legalizing drugs does not imply you may use them on someone without their permission. It's already illegal to give someone else a narcotic they were not prescribed, even though the drug itself is legal. I think all drugs should be legal."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Based on countries that have decriminalized drugs like [Portugal](https://borgenproject.org/decriminalization-of-drugs-in-portugal/), drug use has not significantly increased among the poor population, or at all.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': "Short-term pleasure from addictive drug consumption may lead to [irreversible impairments](https://www.health24.com/Medical/Osteoporosis/News/Graphic-This-drug-will-kill-you-within-two-years-20140709), damaging the consumer's quality of life."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Those with unstable backgrounds are more likely to use drugs which are associated with withdrawal from society.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': '[Alcohol-dependent persons](https://academic.oup.com/alcalc/article/46/2/105/198339) have to face prejudices, although the substance is legal: They are often held responsible for their condition, are subject to social rejection and they are at particular risk for structural discrimination.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The ban on drugs has led to medical discrimination.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Through education, heavy advertising campaigns and controlling the packaging of tobacco, the government can make its negative effects clear despite it being legal. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The legalization of all drugs gives the possibility to control the age group of people participating in the drugs. I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': "Private companies have a history of funding advertising supporting the use of products that are known to be dangerous to one's health, such as tobacco. I think drugs should remain illegal."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': '"Giving up" is preferable to endlessly pursuing an unobtainable goal.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': "Without effective law enforcement, legalizing drugs might fuel criminal gang's economies \\(e.g., illegal trade\\). That's why legalization of drugs is a really bad idea."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalization could provide valuable data in tracking addicts in early stages when purchasing substances frequently. This could create the opportunity to offer addicts support at earlier stages.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Under prohibition, anything related to drugs use \\(like paraphernalia\\) would both be evidence of a crime and likely to be confiscated if found by police â€” this disincentive carrying anything other than the bare necessities to drug use.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalisation does not necessarily mean that drugs will be freely available. It is easier to control and regulate drugs when they are legalised as governments can restrict who can make and sell them.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'This stress would be reduced if the drugs were legal because it would remove the threat of legal danger to any concerned person.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Illegal drug producers and dealers use violence against police and competition. This just doesn't happen in legal businesses. The causes for this is also obvious. A legal business using violence will get fines and possibly be banned from participating in the legal market, and as such is a non-starter. I believe all drugs should be legal."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'In some instances, drug use has increased following legalisation. I believe legalization of drugs is a really bad idea.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'This is biased against those with mental illness. So legalization of drugs is a really bad idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The ban on drugs has criminalized a large number of otherwise innocent individuals.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'The legalisation of drugs may lead to children trying and becoming involved with drugs at a younger age.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'If only leaving syringes was punishable, and not use or possession of drugs, they would put in the extra effort to _not_ break the law at all. I believe all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Historically, the US government has released inaccurate or untruthful information about drugs in an attempt to stop the public from using them. I believe legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Heroin and other opiates cause [negligible](https://rationalwiki.org/wiki/Heroin#Health_effects) direct physical harm to the body. I think all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Unlike companies operating in American borders, drug cartels use violence and threats thereof to increase market share. I think all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'If the war on drugs were won, these jobs would also be lost.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': '[Alcohol-dependent persons](https://academic.oup.com/alcalc/article/46/2/105/198339) have to face prejudices, although the substance is legal: They are often held responsible for their condition, are subject to social rejection and they are at particular risk for structural discrimination.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "If you plan to drug someone with the intent of raping them, you're also able to get a hold of the something as ubiquitous as a benzodiazepine."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Under current laws, these people are being punished for something that this claim suggests they are unable to refrain from doing. If it's not a choice, then we shouldn't punish people for it. Removing the threat of punishment would also encourage people to get treatment. So all drugs should be legal."}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'If a government wanted to put money into harm reduction, it could do so without legalising drugs in order to avoid the costs of enforcing a drug prohibition. It could instead cut other government programs.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': "Drugs being illegal deters many people from using them. That's why legalization of drugs is a really bad idea."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'If this was true, cartels would already be moving over to newer, patented pharmaceuticals, whose costs of production is dwarfed by market price already.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'It will create jobs, not only in distribution but also in drug clinics and counseling centers. I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'There will be less smuggling and less drug-caused conflict. I believe all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'This is not mutually exclusive with legalizing drugs. Both could be done. I think all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalization will allow people to choose the safer drug. Currently law abiding citizens typically choose alcohol or tobacco which is easily in the more dangerous category.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legal companies would be able to take over the drugs-related sector from illegal criminal organisations. I think all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Medical professionals have expressed [negative attitudes](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/23490450) in treating illegal substance abusers, which subsequently negatively impacts their treatment. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The increased tax revenue could enable increased government spending, which [results in more jobs](https://www.americanprogress.org/issues/economy/reports/2011/09/08/10257/government-spending-can-create-jobs-and-it-has/).'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Established entities selling drugs would almost certainly not engage in gun battles on the streets over "[turf](https://www.urbandictionary.com/define.php?term=Turf)".'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Giving a legal framework to the use of certain drugs may help to prevent the development of infectious diseases.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The illegal trade is already there. The legal trade would just drain their customer base. For criminal trade to survive in those conditions it would have to have either cheaper prices or better product. These are not easily achieved agains big corporations. At least the competition would seriously damage their overheads.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalizing drugs would significantly decrease social stigma and discrimination against users who have been incarcerated for employment and education opportunities.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The legalization of drugs will create jobs \\(i.e. people selling in certified shops, people in labs etc.\\).'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Although social prejudice may remain, addicts could seek help far easier if there were no fear of legal repercussions.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Drugs are already easily accessible and quite expensive yet the alcohol industry is still flourishing. It doesn't have to be one or the other. I believe legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "It is unlikely that a low level drug dealer will shift to trafficking human beings the moment drugs get legalised. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The ban on drugs has criminalized a large number of otherwise innocent individuals.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': "Some adults may sell drugs to underaged people to make profit. That's why drugs should remain illegal."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The prohibition forces users, that are otherwise law-abiding citizens, into transactions with more serious law-breakers, opening them up for the possibility to escalate to more serious crimes.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'The lack of regulation surrounding prescribed opioids was caused by pharmaceutical companies [failing to divulge](https://www.drugabuse.gov/drugs-abuse/opioids/opioid-overdose-crisis#three) how addictive opioid painkillers were to the medical community in the 1990s.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'An overdose of heroin is usually fatal without medical help; [during 2016](https://www.cdc.gov/drugoverdose/data/heroin.html), almost 15,500 people died from drug overdoses involving heroin in the United States.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The [majority](http://www.independent.co.uk/news/habits-most-drug-users-are-happy-successful-people-with-a-taste-for-the-good-life-1292155.html) of young individuals consuming illegal substances lead fulfilling and successful lives.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalization of drugs will make people aware of their consequences \\(having a prospectus like medicine with known pros and cons - like marijuana for medical usage\\). So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalizing would lead to a better understanding of addiction in the first place. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'If drugs were legalised, all the ways it could harm other people could be criminalised, such as taking them before controlling dangerous machinery or smoking in public. I believe all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'When obtaining drugs legally people can be sure that the drugs are pure and accurately measured. With the illegal drug market drugs are often mis-sold, inaccurately measured or cut with other substances.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Non-violent dangers could increase, such as syringes being left in parks and other public spaces. This would create a risk of disease and injury to anyone in the area, especially children. I think drugs should remain illegal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalization will help law enforcement agencies.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Established entities selling drugs would almost certainly not engage in gun battles on the streets over "[turf](https://www.urbandictionary.com/define.php?term=Turf)".'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Historically, the US government has only permitted research which [supports their agenda](https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/2015/08/18/feds-limit-research-marijuana-medical-use/31547557/) of prohibition. So all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Some of this emotional harm is directly caused by erroneous negative perceptions of drug use like the ones being perpetrated here. Many people are unfairly vilified for responsibly using drugs, simply because they are illegal. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "When weed was legalized in Colorado for recreational use, the [usage rate](https://www.reuters.com/article/us-colorado-marijuana-idUSKCN0Z702N) among teens and children stayed the same. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Some drugs are highly addictive; [addiction is defined as a disease](https://www.centeronaddiction.org/what-addiction/addiction-disease) by most medical associations.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Cheap drugs means more drugs for the same money, which could lead to more addiction problems.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Illegally acquired date rape drugs could be even more dangerous to victims, as they may be cut with dangerous chemicals. So all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Sensible legal drug policy would uses taxes to keep prices equal or slightly below current black market prices to keep that from occuring. I think drugs should remain illegal.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'If the primary goal is defeating drug dealing and cartels, the most effective way would be just ceasing drug use by everyone. With the "added bonus" that without drug use people will also be healthier and richer. I think drugs should remain illegal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The consumption of psychoactive substances creates religious and transcendental [experiences](https://www.sciencealert.com/how-religion-led-to-humanity-s-love-for-drugs): both are a relevant part of human evolution and significantly shaped human culture. I believe all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': '[A study](http://aic.gov.au/media_library/publications/tandi_pdf/tandi372.pdf) came to the conclusion that alcohol consumption was involved in 47% of homicides in Australia in a six-year period. I believe legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'In 2018, the consumption patterns of most US citizens who used illicit drugs were [unproblematic](https://filtermag.org/2018/09/25/the-invisible-majority-people-whose-drug-use-is-not-problematic/). I believe all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "The issue with these drugs is that it's possible for someone to ingest it unknowingly, after someone dropped them in their drink etc. I think all drugs should be legal."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'It would enable people to easily manage their own pain medication themselves without the trials and tribulations of doctors and presciptions and all those agonizing hoops you need to jump through along the way.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'It is preferable that if people are going to take drugs, the profit of the industry go to the government to use to provide important services rather than to gangs or drug cartels. So all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Since everything is legal, users can instead choose the drugs with the most benefits and the least harms.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalization could provide valuable data in tracking addicts in early stages when purchasing substances frequently. This could create the opportunity to offer addicts support at earlier stages.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Many drugs that are currently illegal have been and are important social tools.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Thousands of people [are killed](https://www.cfr.org/backgrounder/mexicos-drug-war) annually by drug cartels.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'In the long run, the standing of the U.S. government did not suffer from ending the Alcohol Prohibition in the 1930s. Any potential reputational damage from ending marijuana or other prohibitions would be fleeting.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'There is a [correlation](https://americanaddictioncenters.org/rehab-guide/addiction-and-violence) between drug use and \\(violent\\) crime.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Legalization runs the danger of increased drug use that could impair people from doing jobs safely, making work places more dangerous.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Legalization does not treat addicts, treatment and prevention of the addiction do. Both of which can be done with drugs remaining illegal.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': "Addictive drugs increasingly reduce one's ability to do without them, and therefore they can inhibit freedom. So legalization of drugs is a really bad idea."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Young people could use fake IDs to buy drugs, the same way they currently do with alcohol and cigarettes.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The illegal consumption of heroin without any satisfactory hygiene conditions [supports](https://www.drugabuse.gov/publications/research-reports/heroin/why-are-heroin-users-special-risk-contracting-hivaids-hepatitis-b-c) the development of HIV.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalization will help patients by facilitating access to medicines \\(drugs\\) that are currently hard to obtain. I think all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'The climb out of poverty is not helped by wasting resources on ingesting toxic materials.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "It's not a given that the low well-being of drug users' families are a result of the drug use. The confounding variable is likely mental health issues. It's possible \\(and sometimes preferable\\) to solve the mental health issues, while not stopping the drug use."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'If recreational drugs were legal, social events such as parties would have more variety. Drug-friendly events would also have no cause for paranoia. I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Bettering education surrounding date rape and the drugs used for it would improve levels of prevention. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "The black market businesses won't be able to invest in productivity-increasing \\(especially immovable\\) capital, as the threat of being caught discourages such investments. That's why all drugs should be legal."}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'The use of [drugs](https://www.academia.edu/34757965/Why_Recreational_Drug_Use_is_Immoral) that can impair the ability to make moral judgments based on clear, rational \\(and autonomous\\) thinking is immoral.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Psychedelics are often used for [one-off, recreational and spiritual](https://www.livescience.com/61902-psychedelic-drugs-change-personality.html) experiences. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
